# is string method return a boolean that describe the nature of string.
# some methods are mentioned below.

isalpha() returns True if the string consists only of letters and is not blank.

isalnum() returns True if the string consists only of letters and numbers
and is not blank.

isdecimal() returns True if the string consists only of numeric characters
and is not blank

isspace() returns True if the string consists only of spaces, tabs, and newlines and is not blank.

istitle() returns True if the string consists only of words that begin with
an uppercase letter followed by only lowercase letters.


print("hello".isalpha())
print(" ".isspace())
print("hello12".isnumeric())
print("123".isnumeric())
# print(12.isnumeric()) #it will generate an error because it is as string method.


